# Game/Replay/AnimatePlaceHand.elm — EARLY

Replay animation driver for PlaceHand — companion to
`AnimateMergeHand`, extracted as REFACTOR_ELM_REPLAY
B1/Axis Y, 2026-04-22.

A hand card is dragged to an empty spot on the board,
becoming a new single-card stack. Same two-phase async
shape as AnimateMergeHand; the only difference is that the
target endpoint comes from the payload's explicit `loc`
field translated into viewport frame via the live board
rect (rather than measured from another stack's edge).

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. See `AnimateMergeHand.claude` for the
  broader context; this module is its near-twin.

## Interface

Same shape as AnimateMergeHand:

```elm
type alias PrepareResult =
    { source : DragSource
    , grabOffset : Point
    , handCardToMeasure : Card
    }

prepare : { handCard, loc } -> Model -> Maybe PrepareResult

finish :
    { handCard, loc }
    -> Point
    -> Float
    -> DragSource
    -> Point
    -> Model
    -> Maybe Space.AnimationInfo
```

`finish` always returns Just — PlaceHand's target doesn't
depend on any other board stack, so there's nothing to fail
on once the prepare phase has resolved the source.

## Dependencies

- `Game.Replay.Space` — for `handCardSource`,
  `pointInLiveViewport`, `linearPath`, `AnimationInfo`.
- `Game.BoardGeometry` — for `cardHeight`.
- `Game.CardStack` — for `BoardLocation`.
- `Game.WireAction` — for `WA.PlaceHand`.
- `Main.State` — for `Model`, `DragSource`, `PathFrame`,
  `Point`.

## Pointers

- Called from `Game.Replay.Time.prepareHandAnim` /
  `finishHandAnim`.
- Sibling: `AnimateMergeHand`.
